<doc id="1096335" wikidata="Q380650" url="?curid=1096335" title="Barack (brandy)">
<text>Barack () is a type of Hungarian brandy (Pálinka) made of (or flavored with) apricots; an apricot brandy. 

The word &quot;barack&quot; is a collective term for both apricot (in Hungarian , lit. &quot;yellow-peach&quot;) and peach (in Hungarian , lit. &quot;autumn-peach&quot;). Note that the Hungarian word is etymologically related to the English word &#x27;peach&#x27; as well as many words meaning the same in many European languages, and ultimately goes back to , the ancient Greek word for &#x27;Persian&#x27;.

==See also==</text><links>
