<doc id="1096481" wikidata="Q719664" url="?curid=1096481" title="Content industry">
<text>The content industry is an umbrella term that encompasses companies owning and providing mass media and media metadata. This can include music, TV shows, movies, text publications of any kind, ownership of standards, geographic data, and metadata about all and any of the above.

In the Information Age, the content industry comprises an enormous market.

==See also==
* Information industry
* Information technology

